t I dont have a way to know when the timers end.  So I guess this is really two questions.  Is there a way to setup an alert for when the timer ends and Is there a way to control the times through the chat channel.  Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p067.ezboard.com/beqcompanion.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eqcompanion>EQ Companion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1494<br> <font color=#330000>(8/12/05 8:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=411.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alerts</span><hr size=1> Are you creating a 'Timer trigger' or 'Alert trigger'?<br>
<br>
Timer triggers have the 'alert' field where you can type the phrase you want EQC to speak when the timer runs out. Alert triggers just speak the alert out immediately when the phrase if found in the log file.<br>
<br>
It sounds to me, though, that you should be using the 'Mob timer' feature. This feature is for timing mob spawns when you are camping a group of mobs that all have the same spawn time and you are killing them over and over.<br>
<br>
Mob timers work really well in EQ1 where the mob spawn time is fixed. It works pretty well in EQ-II as well, although the spawn times of mobs are more random. For example they could be 9-12 minutes instead of just fixed 22 minutes like in EQ1.<br>
<br>
In the timers-menu you set the mob spawn time. This setting is saved in the INI file so next time you restart EQC it is still set to what you set it last time. If you re-set the time when you have timers running, all the spawn timers will be adjusted accordingly. This way if you did not get the exact spawn time the first time you can adjust it later.<br>
<br>
To create a mob spawn timer you hit Ctrl-F11. The timer is smart in that it knows when the last mob was killed and adjusts the running time accorgingly. For example if you have set the spawn time to be 24 minutes and you kill the first of the 7 mobs; 3 minutes and 27 seconds after you have killed the mob you remember to start the mob timer (you have not killed anything in between). The mob timer starts as an 24 minute timer but the running time of the timer will be pre-set to 3 minutes and 27 seconds.<br>
<br>
Each time you create a new spawn timer EQC acknowledges it using speech.<br>
<br>
Once you have killed all 7 mobs and started their own spawn timers, you do not create any more new spawn timers but rather you just restart the old running timers. You press Ctrl-F1 to restart spawn 1, Ctrl-F5 to restart spawn 5, etc. You can also just hit Ctrl-F12 which will restart the next spawn timer.<br>
<br>
When a mob is about to pop, EQC will speak out 'POP!'.<br>
<br>
You can do all this using the command chat channel as well.<br>
<br>
If you send command 'HELP' to the command chat channel, it shows all the comands and all the spawn timer commands are listed there.<br>
<br>
I am at work right now so I might not remember the syntax exactly, but if I remember correctly:<br>
<br>
"SP ADD" : This creates new spawn timer (Ctrl_F11)<br>
"SP 1" : This restarts spawn timer 1 (Ctrl-F1)<br>
"SP" : This restarts next spawn timer (Ctrl-F12)<br>
"POP" : This tells which mob is up next and how soon or if a mob is already spawned.<br>
<br>
There is even command to designate one of the spawns as a potential 'named' spawn. In EQ1 there are groups of mobs that have one of them potentially spawn as a named mob. You can use the 'NAMED' (if I remember correctly) command to set one of your spawn numbers as this named spawn. When this spawn pops, EQC will announce it as 'Named pop!".<br>
<br>
The reason the spawn timers do not work automatically and restart themselves when EQC sees a mob is killed is because it would more than likely get things messed up eventually. Sometimes you get a roamer for example and you kill it between spawns or sometimes a group member kills a mob so far away from you that your log file does not get the 'kill' message. Having you reset the spawn timers manually ensures they are accurate. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p067.ezboard.com/beqcompanion.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eqcompanion>EQ Companion</A> at: 8/12/05 8:53 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=411.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=411.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=411.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=411.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.threadControl?topicID=411.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://p067.ezboard.com/feqcompanionfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=411.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://p067.